### Mock Playwright API Requests with Custom JSON Response

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/mock.md

This snippet demonstrates how to intercept and mock specific API requests within Playwright tests across multiple programming languages. It configures a route to intercept calls matching a URL pattern (e.g., `*/**/api/v1/fruits`), fulfills these requests with a custom, hardcoded JSON response, and then navigates to a page that depends on this API. Finally, it asserts that the mocked data is correctly displayed on the page, ensuring no actual network requests are made to the original API endpoint.

```javascript
test("mocks a fruit and doesn't call api", async ({ page }) => {
  // Mock the api call before navigating
  await page.route('*/**/api/v1/fruits', async route => {
    const json = [{ name: 'Strawberry', id: 21 }];
    await route.fulfill({ json });
  });
  // Go to the page
  await page.goto('https://demo.playwright.dev/api-mocking');

  // Assert that the Strawberry fruit is visible
  await expect(page.getByText('Strawberry')).toBeVisible();
});
```

```python
async def test_mock_the_fruit_api(page: Page):
    async def handle(route: Route):
        json = [{"name": "Strawberry", "id": 21}]
        # fulfill the route with the mock data
        await route.fulfill(json=json)

    # Intercept the route to the fruit API
    await page.route("*/**/api/v1/fruits", handle)

    # Go to the page
    await page.goto("https://demo.playwright.dev/api-mocking")

    # Assert that the Strawberry fruit is visible
    await expect(page.get_by_text("Strawberry")).to_be_visible()
```

