### Playwright: Mock API Responses with Page Routing

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/network.md

Illustrates how to intercept and fulfill network requests using `page.route` to mock API endpoints. This allows tests to control the responses from backend services by providing custom status codes and body content for specific URLs.

```js
await page.route('**/api/fetch_data', route => route.fulfill({
  status: 200,
  body: testData,
}));
await page.goto('https://example.com');
```

```java
page.route("**/api/fetch_data", route -> route.fulfill(new Route.FulfillOptions()
  .setStatus(200)
  .setBody(testData)));
page.navigate("https://example.com");
```

```python async
await page.route(
    "**/api/fetch_data",
    lambda route: route.fulfill(status=200, body=test_data))
await page.goto("https://example.com")
```

```python sync
page.route(
    "**/api/fetch_data",
