### Replay API Requests from HAR in Playwright Tests

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/mock.md

This code demonstrates how to configure Playwright to replay API requests from a HAR file during a test execution. By setting `update: false`, the test will serve responses from the specified HAR file, effectively mocking network interactions. This is useful for testing frontend logic without hitting actual backend services.

```javascript
test('gets the json from HAR and checks the new fruit has been added', async ({ page }) => {
  // Replay API requests from HAR.
  // Either use a matching response from the HAR,
  // or abort the request if nothing matches.
  await page.routeFromHAR('./hars/fruit.har', {
    url: '*/**/api/v1/fruits',
    update: false,
  });

  // Go to the page
  await page.goto('https://demo.playwright.dev/api-mocking');

  // Assert that the Playwright fruit is visible
  await expect(page.getByText('Playwright', { exact: true })).toBeVisible();
});
```

```python
async def test_gets_the_json_from_har_and_checks_the_new_fruit_has_been_added(page: Page):
    # Replay API requests from HAR.
    # Either use a matching response from the HAR,
    # or abort the request if nothing matches.
    await page.route_from_har("./hars/fruit.har", url="*/**/api/v1/fruits", update=False)

    # Go to the page
    await page.goto("https://demo.playwright.dev/api-mocking")

    # Assert that the Playwright fruit is visible
    await expect(page.get_by_text("Playwright", exact=True)).to_be_visible()
```

