### Mock Network Requests at Context Level in Playwright Test

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/network.md

Demonstrates how to block CSS requests for all tests in a file using context-level route configuration. This approach applies network mocking to all pages within the browser context, executed before each test runs.

```javascript
import { test, expect } from '@playwright/test';

test.beforeEach(async ({ context }) => {
  // Block any css requests for each test in this file.
  await context.route(/.css$/, route => route.abort());
});

test('loads page without css', async ({ page }) => {
  await page.goto('https://playwright.dev');
  // ... test goes here
});
```

