### Reuse Authentication State with Playwright API and BrowserContext (Java)

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/api-testing-java.md

This Java snippet demonstrates how to manage and reuse authentication state across Playwright contexts. It logs in via an API request, retrieves the `storageState` from the authenticated `APIRequestContext`, and then creates a new `BrowserContext` pre-populated with this saved state, enabling authenticated browser sessions without UI login.

```java
APIRequestContext requestContext = playwright.request().newContext(
  new APIRequest.NewContextOptions().setHttpCredentials("user", "passwd"));
requestContext.get("https://api.example.com/login");
// Save storage state into a variable.
String state = requestContext.storageState();

// Create a new context with the saved storage state.
BrowserContext context = browser.newContext(new Browser.NewContextOptions().setStorageState(state));
```

