### Playwright: Mock API Responses with Browser Context Routing

Source: https://github.com/microsoft/playwright/blob/main/docs/src/network.md

Explains how to set up request interception rules using `browserContext.route`. This method applies the routing logic to all pages within the browser context, including newly opened tabs and popups, making it suitable for global API mocking.

```js
await browserContext.route('**/api/login', route => route.fulfill({
  status: 200,
  body: 'accept',
}));
await page.goto('https://example.com');
```

```java
browserContext.route("**/api/login", route -> route.fulfill(new Route.FulfillOptions()
